Loading data

Load the database from Stata:

dbRelations <- read_dta('./data/interLoans/cen_deu_1997-06_2001-06_todas_ent_fcieras.dta') %>%
              dplyr::select(., FECHAdata, IDENT_ACREEDORA, IDENT_DEUDORA,           PRESTAMOS) %>%
              dplyr::filter(., !is.na(IDENT_DEUDORA)) %>%
              dplyr::mutate(., FECHAdata = ymd("1960-01-01")+months(FECHAdata))
dbFcialEnts <- read_dta('./data/DBbanks/capital-allEntities-Monthly.dta', col_select = c(IDent, FECHAdata, bNombre, grupoIDUni, Activo, ActivoR,
                      ALIQs1_1ratio, APRamplio, C8Est_w, CAR_IRR_3A6,
                      P_LOANS_ARS_RATE, P_DEP_ARS_RATE, P_ROA, C8_E)) %>%
                dplyr::mutate(., FECHAdata = ymd("1960-01-01")+months(FECHAdata),                        IDENT_ACREEDORA = IDent) %>%
                filter(., FECHAdata<ymd("2002-01-01") & FECHAdata>ymd("1997-05-01"))

Weighting relations

Now we build the wights of each link. We backup the data on Assets and Loans from dbFcialEnts and enter into the dbRelations data frame.

relations <- dbRelations %>%
              filter(., IDENT_ACREEDORA != IDENT_DEUDORA) %>%
              dplyr::left_join(., dbFcialEnts, by = c('IDENT_ACREEDORA', 'FECHAdata'))

Oh missing values!

From creditors perspective

The following entities appear in the Central de deudores but not anymore in the balance de saldos:

missCreditors <- dplyr::anti_join(relations, dbFcialEnts, 
                                  by=c('FECHAdata', 'IDENT_ACREEDORA'))

The 318 Banco de Salta SA which was absorbed by Banco Macro on November 1999. I have detailed data only till Sep-1999. I could get more aggregated data if necesary from the balance resumido. Caja de crdito Universo Cooperativa Limitada 64123 did not report its balance in 2000-10. I treat it as a missing value.

I impute this missing values. Replace with the previous value

toAddSalta <- filter(dbFcialEnts, FECHAdata == ym(199909) &IDent == 318) %>%
            mutate(., FECHAdata = ym(199910))
toAddUniverso <- filter(dbFcialEnts, FECHAdata == ym(200009) &IDent == 64123) %>%
                  mutate(., FECHAdata = ym(200010))
dbFcialEnts <- bind_rows(dbFcialEnts, toAddSalta, toAddUniverso)

From debtors perspective

Verify that all nodes involved in relations are in dbFcialEnts. The following table shows the relations in which a debtor does not appear in dbFcialEnts. anti_join(), returns rows in relations without a match in dbFcialEnts.

missDebtors <- anti_join(relations, 
                    mutate(dbFcialEnts, IDENT_DEUDORA = IDent),
                    by=c('FECHAdata', 'IDENT_DEUDORA')) %>%
                  group_by(., IDENT_DEUDORA) %>%
                  summarise(n = n())
## `summarise()` ungrouping output (override with `.groups` argument)

This could be due to debtors disappearing. A debtor disappears as a financial entitites but the debts do not expire, such that active financial entities still report the debts.

I exclude these relations from the relations tibble. We exclude those observations and select a specific month, say, 1999m12

#relations <- filter(relations, !is.na(IDent))
atDate <- ymd("1999-12-01")
thisRelations <- dplyr::filter(relations, FECHAdata == atDate) %$% 
                  .[ !(.$IDENT_DEUDORA %in% missDebtors$IDENT_DEUDORA),  ] %>%
                  dplyr::mutate(., WEIGHT = PRESTAMOS/APRamplio) %>%
                  dplyr::select(., IDENT_ACREEDORA, IDENT_DEUDORA, WEIGHT)
nodes <- filter(dbFcialEnts, FECHAdata==atDate) %>%
          dplyr::select(., !FECHAdata)

When did these bank end in entidades.dta?

dbEnts <- read_dta('../BasesBCRA-IEF/entidades/entidades.dta') %>%

entsDates <- dbEnts %>%

We can plot g

library(ggraph) 
## Warning: package 'ggraph' was built under R version 4.0.3
ggraph(g, layout='fr', weights=WEIGHT ) +
  geom_edge_link() +
  geom_node_point(aes(size = centrality_pagerank())) +
  theme(legend.position = 'bottom')

ggraph(g, layout='fr', weights=WEIGHT ) +
  geom_edge_link(aes(width=WEIGHT, colour=stat(index))) +
  geom_node_point(aes(size = Activo), colour='blue', alpha=.2) +
  geom_node_text(aes(label = bNombre), repel=TRUE) + 
  theme(legend.position = 'bottom')

## Interactive plot Using visNetwork package. I use the same g object from iGraph

pTblNodes <- nodes %>%
  dplyr::select(., IDent, bNombre, Activo) %>%
  dplyr::transmute(., id=IDent, label=bNombre, value=Activo, title=str_c(bNombre, ', $ ', (Activo/10000), ' mill.'))

pTblRelations <- thisRelations %>%
  dplyr::transmute(., from=IDENT_ACREEDORA, to=IDENT_DEUDORA, value=WEIGHT, arrows='to')

visNetwork(nodes = pTblNodes, edges = pTblRelations)%>% 
  visOptions(highlightNearest = TRUE, nodesIdSelection = TRUE) %>%
  visInteraction(navigationButtons = TRUE) %>%
  visConfigure(enabled = TRUE)
